A 60% chance of thundershowers has been predicted across the province today, while only a 30% is expected on Sunday. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service says Gauteng residents should expect thundershowers throughout the weekend.A 60% chance of thundershowers has been predicted across the province today, while only a 30% is expected on Sunday.Recent downpours have had a positive impact on dam levels, including the Vaal River system.According to Joburg Water, Vaal Dam levels have risen and now stand at 54.54%.Forecaster Lulama Pheme says: We are expecting showers. It will be cloudy at times with showers. WATCH: Facing a dry future: How bad is the water crisis really?(Edited by Shimoney Regter)